						               													<description>A simple trivia game played on a map of the German State of Schleswig-Holstein.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A long track winds around the State, starting in Hamburg and ending on the Isle of Sylt. Movement is decided by a die. There are four categories of questions:&amp;#10;A = General knowledge&amp;#10;K = Culture&amp;#10;W = Economic&amp;#10;P = Politics and History&amp;#10;Obviously, all the 500 questions in the game have some connection to Schleswig Holstein.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There is an interesting shortcut that may be taken where no questions are asked. Instead you roll the die and if you get a number from 1 to 5, you move two spaces. But if you roll a 6, you must go back 15 spaces.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;First to reach the end (Ziel) wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On a little bit of extra trivia, the board shows clearly that the Eastern neighbour to Schleswig-Holstein is, in fact, the DDR (East Germany). As the game was published in 1989 and the wall came down that year, then this might be the last non-historical game to feature the DDR as a neighbouring country.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
